    <p>
      <i>
        <sup>1</sup> Adjusted OCI margins are calculated as adjusted OCI divided by revenues net of excise taxes.</i>
    </p>
    <p>
      <b>Shipment Volume</b>
    </p>
    <p>
      <b>Third Quarter</b>
    </p>
    <ul class="bwlistdisc">
      <li>
Oral tobacco products segment reported domestic shipment volume increased 1.3%,<b></b>primarily driven by trade inventory movements, the industry’s growth rate and calendar differences, partially offset by retail share losses and other factors. When adjusted for trade inventory movements and calendar differences, oral tobacco products segment shipment volume decreased by an estimated 2%.
</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      <b>First Nine Months</b>
    </p>
    <ul class="bwlistdisc">
      <li>
Oral tobacco products segment reported domestic shipment volume decreased 1.8%,<b></b>primarily driven by retail share losses and trade inventory movements, partially offset by calendar differences, the industry’s growth rate and other factors. When adjusted for trade inventory movements and calendar differences, oral tobacco products segment shipment volume decreased by an estimated 1.5%.
</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
Total oral tobacco industry volume was essentially unchanged for the six months ended September 30, 2022, as the growth in oral nicotine pouches was offset by declining MST volumes
</p>
